  "explain": {
    "jetMatrix": "A jet matrix records all derivatives of a kernel at one point. The entry (i,j) is partial_s^i partial_t^j K(s0,s0)/(i!j!). If the kernel were positive, every such matrix would be positive semidefinite.",
    "lambda": "The lowest eigenvector of the 9-jet matrix gives a local linear test Lambda_a(f)=sum e_k(a) f^(k)(a)/k!.  The active endpoint obstruction is the moving family of these tests.",
    "schur": "R collects the Lambda_a traces.  Splitting functions into ker R and its orthogonal complement turns the proof into a Schur/Douglas range problem."
